statement:
Noetherian Jacobson rings. 
\begin{enumerate} 
\item Any Noetherian domain $R$ of dimension $1$ with infinitely many primes is Jacobson. 
\item Any Noetherian ring such that every prime \mathfrak p is either maximal or contained in infinitely many prime ideals is Jacobson. 
\end{enumerate}

